13/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Boris Trajkovski spoke with US Secretary of State Colin Powell Friday (11 April) on the telephone. Powell thanked him for the support Macedonia has shown during the US-led military campaign in Iraq. Trajkovski's office said they also discussed post-war reconstruction and Macedonia's possible participation in the process. The country plans to contribute a small contingent, providing both medial and military support. (Utrinski Vesnik - 12/04/03; MIA, A1 TV - 11/04/03)
